  75,22,On that Day ЋєsomeЋЇ faces will be bright
  75,23,looking at their Lord
  75,24,And ЋєotherЋЇ faces will be gloomy
  75,25,anticipating something devastating to befall them
  75,26,But no! ЋєBeware of the dayЋЇ when the soul reaches the collar bone Ћєas it leavesЋЇ
  75,27,"and it will be said, вАЬIs there any healer Ћєwho can save this lifeЋЇ?вАЭ"
  75,28,And the dying person realizes it is ЋєtheirЋЇ time to depart
  75,29,and ЋєthenЋЇ their feet are tied together Ћєin a shroudЋЇ
