  76,6,"ЋєfromЋЇ a spring where GodвАЩs servants will drink, flowing at their will"
  76,7,They Ћєare those whoЋЇ fulfil ЋєtheirЋЇ vows and fear a Day of sweeping horror
  76,8,"and give foodвАФdespite their desire for itвАФto the poor, the orphan, and the captive"
  76,9,"Ћєsaying to themselves,ЋЇ вАЬWe feed you only for the sake of God, seeking neither reward nor thanks from you"
  76,10,We fear from our Lord a horribly distressful Day.вАЭ
  76,11,"So God will deliver them from the horror of that Day, and grant them radiance and joy"
  76,12,and reward them for their perseverance with a Garden Ћєin ParadiseЋЇ and Ћєgarments ofЋЇ silk
  76,13,"There they will be reclining on ЋєcanopiedЋЇ couches, never seeing scorching heat or bitter cold"
  76,14,"The GardenвАЩs shade will be right above them, and its fruit will be made very easy to reach"
  76,15,They will be waited on with silver vessels and cups of crystalвАФ
  76,16,"crystalline silver, filled precisely as desired"
  76,17,And they will be given a drink Ћєof pure wineЋЇ flavoured with ginger
  76,18,"from a spring there, called Salsab√Ѓl"
  76,19,"They will be waited on by eternal youths. If you saw them, you would think they were scattered pearls"
  76,20,"And if you looked around, you would see ЋєindescribableЋЇ bliss and a vast kingdom"
  76,21,"The virtuous will be ЋєdressedЋЇ in garments of fine green silk and rich brocade, and adorned with bracelets of silver, and their Lord will give them a purifying drink"
  76,22,"ЋєAnd they will be told,ЋЇ вАЬAll this is surely a reward for you. Your striving has been appreciated.вАЭ"
  76,23,"Indeed, it is We Who have revealed the Quran to you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ in stages"
  76,24,"So be patient with your LordвАЩs decree, and do not yield to any evildoer or ЋєstaunchЋЇ disbeliever from among them"
  76,25,ЋєAlwaysЋЇ remember the Name of your Lord morning and evening
  76,26,"and prostrate before Him during part of the night,¬†and glorify Him long at night"
  76,27,"Surely those ЋєpagansЋЇ love this fleeting world, ЋєtotallyЋЇ neglecting a weighty Day ahead of them"
  76,28,"It is We Who created them and perfected their ЋєphysicalЋЇ form. But if We will, We can easily replace them with others"
  76,29,Surely this is a reminder. So let whoever wills take the ЋєRightЋЇ Way to their Lord
  76,30,"But you cannot will Ћєto do soЋЇ unless God wills. Indeed, God is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  76,31,"He admits whoever He wills into His mercy. As for the wrongdoers, He has prepared for them a painful punishment"
